`crates/steno/src/bin/viz_data/` is a standalone CLI binary (not a library other crates depend on) that turns `dict.steno`'s source text into `out/viz-data.json`, the sole data file `viz/index.html` reads to render a category → stroke-choice → outline drill-down UI. Nothing outside this directory calls into it; its only external contracts are the `dict.steno` source format on input and the JSON wire shape on output.

The pipeline has a fixed order, wired in `main.rs`: `comments::scan`/`scan_desc` read raw source text for `##`/`###` markers *independently* of `expand_dict`'s parse of the same source — if dict.steno's comment syntax changes, both parsers must move together. `build::build` then does two passes: it renders leaf `Node`s keyed by `tree::group_key` (which collapses one-liner/multi-line variants of a stroke into one node), then hands leaf positions (via `tree::position`) to `axis::group` to bucket sibling choices, and finally `grouping::apply_grouping` splices the resulting axis nodes and children back into the `Tree`. `json::to_json` serializes the finished `Tree` to the exact camelCase shape `viz/index.html` parses.

Two string-key conventions are shared across files and must stay in sync: the synthetic `cat:{label}` root-position key, produced by `tree::position` and consumed by `axis::group`'s `children_of` map and again by `grouping::apply_grouping`'s category-root lookup — a mismatch here fails silently (roots just keep stale/empty children, no error). The synthetic axis key format `#{line}.{idx}` is produced in `axis.rs` and consumed opaquely elsewhere as just another node key. Ordering is a subtree-wide invariant: every stage (comments scan, node/category dedup in `build.rs`, axis bucketing, `node_order` in `tree.rs`, JSON emission) preserves first-seen/file order rather than sorting, and `json.rs`'s output correctness depends on `node_order` staying a superset match with `nodes` — several stages silently drop or skip on key mismatches instead of erroring, so key-format changes are the most likely source of silent breakage rather than crashes.

`tree.rs` defines the shared `Tree`/`Node`/`Axis` data model and the `group_key`/`position` key-derivation logic that both `build.rs` and `axis.rs`/`grouping.rs` depend on. `axis.rs` is the bucketing algorithm deciding which sibling leaves become one axis choice node. `grouping.rs` is the second pass that mutates the tree with axis results. `comments.rs` is the only file that reads `dict.steno`'s raw text rather than its parsed structure. `json.rs` owns the one place the wire format is defined, duplicated only informally in `viz/index.html` (outside this crate). `main.rs` is pure orchestration with no tree-building logic of its own.